'''''Intensity''''' is a 1988 [[action game|action]] game designed by [[Andrew Braybrook]], developed by [[Graftgold]], and published by [[Firebird Software]]. It was released for the [[Commodore 64]] and [[ZX Spectrum]] platforms.

''Intensity'' received generally positive reviews from video game critics and had underwhelming sales.

==Gameplay==
''Intensity'' is an [[action game|action]] game. The gameplay involves shooting aliens who are attacking a space station and rescuing colonists.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/the-games-machine-10/page/n15/mode/2up|title=The Games Machine Issue 10}}</ref>

==Development==
''Intensity'' was designed by [[Andrew Braybrook]], known for designing [[Morpheus (1987 video game)|''Morpheus'']], ''[[Paradroid]]'', and ''[[Uridium]]''. It was published by [[Firebird Software]].<ref>{{cite magazine|magazine=[[The Games Machine]]|title=Previews|date=September 1988|page=16|issue=10|url=https://archive.org/stream/the-games-machine-10/TheGamesMachine10#page/n15/mode/2up}}</ref> It took Braybrook nine months to write and design the game.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.retrogamer.net/profiles/developer/andrew-braybrook/|title=Andrew Braybrook|author=Retro Gamer Team|work=[[Retro Gamer]]|date=3 June 2014|access-date=4 November 2020}}</ref> It was released for the [[Commodore 64]] and [[ZX Spectrum]] in 1988.

